                             106:        return head;                                                                                                                                                            
                             107:}                                                                                                                                                                               
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             </code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Root Cause Analysis                                                                                                                                                              
                                - The function `condition_free_list_type()` in `src/shared/condition.c` iterates over the list of `Condition` objects (using `LIST_FOREACH`) and calls                           
                             `condition_free(c)` on matching elements, but never unlinks them from the list. This leaves dangling `next`/`prev` pointers and a stale `head` pointer, causing                     
                             heap-use-after-free when the list is later traversed or freed again (e.g. in `link_config_free()`).                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Patch Outline                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - Rewrite `condition_free_list_type()` to:                                                                                                                                       
                                  a. Iterate safely over the list, caching the next pointer before any removal.                                                                                                  
                                  b. For each node `c` matching the `type` (or all nodes if `type < 0`):                                                                                                         
                                     i.   Remove `c` from the list using `LIST_REMOVE(conditions, head, c)`.                                                                                                     
                                     ii.  Free the node via `condition_free(c)`.                                                                                                                                 
                                  c. Return the updated `head` pointer (which will be `NULL` if all nodes were removed when `type < 0`).                                                                         
                                  d. Preserve the existing assertion to verify that when `type < 0`, the resulting `head` is indeed `NULL`.                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Detailed Steps                                                                                                                                                                   
                                a. Open `src/shared/condition.c` and locate `condition_free_list_type()`.                                                                                                        
                                b. Replace the existing implementation:                                                                                                                                          
                                   ```c                                                                                                                                                                          
                                   Condition* condition_free_list_type(Condition *head, ConditionType type) {                                                                                                    
                                           LIST_FOREACH(conditions, c, head)                                                                                                                                     
                                                   if (type < 0 || c->type == type) {                                                                                                                            
                                                           condition_free(c);                                                                                                                                    
                                                   }                                                                                                                                                             
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                           assert(type >= 0 || !head);                                                                                                                                           
                                           return head;                                                                                                                                                          
                                   }                                                                                                                                                                             
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                   with:                                                                                                                                                                         
                                   ```c                                                                                                                                                                          
                                   Condition* condition_free_list_type(Condition *head, ConditionType type) {                                                                                                    
                                       Condition *c, *n;                                                                                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                       /* Iterate safely, caching next before possible removal */                                                                                                                
                                       LIST_FOREACH_WITH_NEXT(conditions, c, n, head) {                                                                                                                          
                                           if (type < 0 || c->type == type) {                                                                                                                                    
                                               /* Unlink c from the list; updates head if c was first */                                                                                                         
                                               LIST_REMOVE(conditions, head, c);                                                                                                                                 
                                               /* Free parameters and the struct itself */                                                                                                                       
                                               condition_free(c);                                                                                                                                                
                                           }                                                                                                                                                                     
                                       }                                                                                                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                       /* If type < 0, all nodes must have been removed */                                                                                                                       
                                       assert(type >= 0 || head == NULL);                                                                                                                                        
                                       return head;                                                                                                                                                              
                                   }                                                                                                                                                                             
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                c. Rebuild and rerun the fuzz target (`fuzz-link-parser`) under AddressSanitizer to confirm the UAF no longer reproduces.                                                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Justification                                                                                                                                                                    
                                - **Preserves existing logic**:                                                                                                                                                  
                                  - For `type >= 0`, only nodes of that type are freed; others remain in the list in their original order and linkage.                                                           
                                  - For `type < 0` (used by `condition_free_list()`), all nodes are removed and freed, leaving `head == NULL`.                                                                   
                                - **Eliminates use-after-free**:                                                                                                                                                 
                                  - By unlinking nodes before freeing, no dangling pointers remain in the list, preventing subsequent traversals from accessing freed memory.                                    
                                - **Maintains assertions**:                                                                                                                                                      
                                  - The existing `assert(type >= 0 || !head)` is preserved, ensuring that callers relying on `condition_free_list()` still see an empty list.                                    
                                - **Minimal and localized change**:                                                                                                                                              
                                  - Only `condition_free_list_type()` is modified. No external libraries, fuzz harnesses, or test code are touched.                                                              
                                - **Macros leveraged correctly**:                                                                                                                                                
                                  - `LIST_FOREACH_WITH_NEXT` safely captures the next pointer before removal.                                                                                                    
                                  - `LIST_REMOVE` updates `head` and the neighboring nodes pointers, ensuring list integrity.                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Potential Side Effects & Mitigation                                                                                                                                              
                                - **Order of survivors**: Unremoved nodes retain their original ordering because `LIST_REMOVE` only severs matching nodes. No reversal or reordering occurs.                     
                                - **Concurrent modifications**: This function is not used concurrently. No additional locking is required.                                                                       
                                - **Assertion failure**: If some code incorrectly relies on non-`NULL` head after a full-list free, the assertion will catch it during testing. Fix callers if                   
                             such behavior is needed, but the semantic contract of `condition_free_list()` is to clear the list.                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             6. Verification                                                                                                                                                                     
                                - Add or re-enable existing unit tests for `condition_free_list_type()` and `condition_free_list()`, verifying:                                                                  
                                   Partial removal (specific `ConditionType`) leaves correct nodes.                                                                                                             
                                   Full removal (`type < 0`) yields `NULL` head and no memory leaks.                                                                                                            
                                - Re-run the `fuzz-link-parser` target under AddressSanitizer to confirm no UAF.                                                                                                 
                                - Run the full systemd test suite to ensure no regressions.                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                     
                             ===Evaluation End===

                             INFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-size=2g --platform linux/amd64 --rm -i -e HELPER=True -e ARCHITECTURE=x86_64 -v                                                
                             /tasks_new/systemd_systemd-full-001/fuzz-tooling/build/out/systemd:/out -v /tmp/tmp1vv_vdg9:/testcase -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.3.0 reproduce                          
                             fuzz-link-parser -runs=100.                                                                                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ===Evaluation Report===                                                                                                                                                             
                             # Evaluation Report                                                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Summary                                                                                                                                                                          
                             An AddressSanitizer report during fuzzing of `fuzz-link-parser` revealed a heap-use-after-free in `condition_free_list_type` (src/shared/condition.c). A proposed                   
                             patch replaced the single-pass `LIST_FOREACH` loop with a two-pointer safe iteration using `LIST_FOREACH_WITH_NEXT`, manually unlinked matching nodes with                          
                             `LIST_REMOVE`, and added an assertion that if `type < 0` then the list is empty. Applying this patch triggered compilation errors: the macros own declarations of                  
                             `c` and `n` shadow the locally declared variables, leading to declaration shadows a local variable errors (treated as fatal under `-Werror`) and unused-variable                  
                             warnings.                                                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Description                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Initial issue                                                                                                                                                                       
                              While fuzzing the link parser, AddressSanitizer flagged a heap-use-after-free at `condition_free_list_type` in `src/shared/condition.c:100:9`. The log shows that                 
                             freeing a `Condition` node via `condition_free` left later accesses to freed memory within the same traversal. The backtrace traces through `link_config_free`,                     
                             `link_load_one`, and `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Key observations from the ASAN log                                                                                                                                                  
                              The offending read occurs in `condition_free_list_type` after a prior free.                                                                                                       
                              The list is traversed with `LIST_FOREACH(conditions, c, head)`, and matching nodes are freed in place, invalidating the next pointer.                                             
                              The freed region is 32 bytes, and the subsequent 8-byte read is into a freed block.                                                                                               
                              The assertion at the end of the function checks that if `type < 0`, no nodes remain, but does not prevent invalid memory access during iteration.                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Patch attempt                                                                                                                                                                       
                              In `src/shared/condition.c`, lines around the original loop:                                                                                                                      
                               ```                                                                                                                                                                               
                               -        LIST_FOREACH(conditions, c, head)                                                                                                                                        
                               +        Condition *c, *n;                                                                                                                                                        
                               +        /* Iterate safely, caching next before possible removal */                                                                                                               
                               +        LIST_FOREACH_WITH_NEXT(conditions, c, n, head) {                                                                                                                         
                               +                if (type < 0 || c->type == type) {                                                                                                                               
                               +                        /* Unlink c from the list; updates head if c was first */                                                                                                
                               +                        LIST_REMOVE(conditions, head, c);                                                                                                                        
                               +                        /* Free parameters and the struct itself */                                                                                                              
                               +                        condition_free(c);                                                                                                                                       
                               +                }                                                                                                                                                                
                               +        }                                                                                                                                                                        
                               +        /* If type < 0, all nodes must have been removed */                                                                                                                      
                               +        assert(type >= 0 || head == NULL);                                                                                                                                       
                               ```                                                                                                                                                                               
                              The intention was to capture `n` before each potential removal, then unlink and free `c` safely.                                                                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Patch result                                                                                                                                                                        
                              Compilation errors due to variable shadowing:                                                                                                                                     
                               ```                                                                                                                                                                               
                               error: declaration shadows a local variable [-Werror,-Wshadow]                                                                                                                    
                                 LIST_FOREACH_WITH_NEXT(conditions, c, n, head) {                                                                                                                                
                                                          ^          ~                                                                                                                                           
                               note: previous declaration is here                                                                                                                                                
                                 Condition *c, *n;                                                                                                                                                               
                                                      ^                                                                                                                                                          
                               ```                                                                                                                                                                               
                              The `LIST_FOREACH_WITH_NEXT` macro itself declares new `c` and `n` variables, conflicting with the explicitly declared ones. The preexisting declarations also                    
                             become unused, causing warnings.                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             Areas for further investigation                                                                                                                                                     
                              The definitions of `LIST_FOREACH`, `LIST_FOREACH_WITH_NEXT`, and `LIST_REMOVE` in `src/shared/list.h` to understand their expansion and variable scopes.                          
                              The original single-pass loop in `condition_free_list_type` to see how `head` and `c` are updated.                                                                                
                              How `condition_free` and related helper functions (`condition_free_list`, `link_config_free`) handle internal pointers and list integrity.                                        
                              The usage patterns of `condition_free_list_type` elsewhere in the codebase, and how assertions on `head` are employed.

                             src/basic/list.h:130-142                                                                                                                                                            
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             130:#define LIST_JUST_US(name, item)                                        \                                                                                                       
                             131:        ({                                                              \                                                                                                       
                             132:                typeof(*(item)) *_item = (item);                        \                                                                                                       
                             133:                !(_item)->name##_prev && !(_item)->name##_next;         \                                                                                                       
                             134:        })                                                                                                                                                                      
                             135:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             136:/* The type of the iterator 'i' is automatically determined by the type of 'head', and declared in the                                                                          
                             137: * loop. Hence, do not declare the same variable in the outer scope. Sometimes, we set 'head' through                                                                           
                             138: * hashmap_get(). In that case, you need to explicitly cast the result. */                                                                                                      
                             139:#define LIST_FOREACH_WITH_NEXT(name,i,n,head)                           \                                                                                                       
                             140:        for (typeof(*(head)) *n, *i = (head); i && (n = i->name##_next, true); i = n)                                                                                           
                             141:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             142:#define LIST_FOREACH(name,i,head)                                       \                                                                                                       
                             ```

                             56:                else {                                                  \

                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             204:        if (isempty(rvalue)) {

                             217:        /* Drop previous assignment. */

                             src/basic/list.h:47-62                                                                                                                                                              
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             47:/* Remove an item from the list */                                                                                                                                               
                             48:#define LIST_REMOVE(name,head,item)                                     \                                                                                                        
                             49:        ({                                                              \                                                                                                        
                             50:                typeof(*(head)) **_head = &(head), *_item = (item);     \                                                                                                        
                             51:                assert(_item);                                          \                                                                                                        
                             52:                if (_item->name##_next)                                 \                                                                                                        
                             53:                        _item->name##_next->name##_prev = _item->name##_prev; \                                                                                                  
                             54:                if (_item->name##_prev)                                 \                                                                                                        
                             55:                        _item->name##_prev->name##_next = _item->name##_next; \                                                                                                  
                             56:                else {                                                  \                                                                                                        
                             57:                        assert(*_head == _item);                        \                                                                                                        
                             58:                        *_head = _item->name##_next;                    \                                                                                                        
                             59:                }                                                       \                                                                                                        
                             60:                _item->name##_next = _item->name##_prev = NULL;         \                                                                                                        
                             61:                _item;                                                  \                                                                                                        
                             62:        })                                                                                                                                                                       
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>                                                                                                                                                                             
                             <code>                                                                                                                                                                              
                             src/basic/list.h:136-142                                                                                                                                                            
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             136:/* The type of the iterator 'i' is automatically determined by the type of 'head', and declared in the                                                                          
                             137: * loop. Hence, do not declare the same variable in the outer scope. Sometimes, we set 'head' through                                                                           
                             138: * hashmap_get(). In that case, you need to explicitly cast the result. */                                                                                                      
                             139:#define LIST_FOREACH_WITH_NEXT(name,i,n,head)                           \                                                                                                       
                             140:        for (typeof(*(head)) *n, *i = (head); i && (n = i->name##_next, true); i = n)                                                                                           
                             141:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             142:#define LIST_FOREACH(name,i,head)                                       \                                                                                                       
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </code>

                             src/basic/list.h:195-204                                                                                                                                                            
                             ```                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             195:#define LIST_CLEAR(name, head, free_func)       \                                                                                                                               
                             196:        _LIST_CLEAR(name, head, free_func, UNIQ_T(elem, UNIQ))                                                                                                                  
                             197:                                                                                                                                                                                
                             198:/* Clear the list, destroying each element with free_func */                                                                                                                    
                             199:#define _LIST_CLEAR(name, head, free_func, elem)        \                                                                                                                       
                             200:        ({                                              \                                                                                                                       
                             201:                typeof(head) elem;                      \                                                                                                                       
                             202:                while ((elem = LIST_POP(name, head)))   \                                                                                                                       
                             203:                        free_func(elem);                \                                                                                                                       
                             204:                head;                                   \                                                                                                                       
                             ```

                             </code_snippets>                                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             ## Fix Strategy                                                                                                                                                                     
                             <fix_strategy>                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             1. Overview of the fix                                                                                                                                                              
                                Replace the entire body of `condition_free_list_type` in `src/shared/condition.c` with two simple, macro-based code paths:                                                       
                                a) A full clear when `type < 0` using the existing `LIST_CLEAR` macro (which caches the next pointer before freeing and sets `head` to `NULL`).                                  
                                b) A selective traversal when `type >= 0` using `LIST_FOREACH_WITH_NEXT` plus `LIST_REMOVE`, leveraging the macros own local iterator declarations (thus                        
                             avoiding any `-Wshadow` conflicts) and ensuring safe free-before-advance iteration (no heap-use-after-free).                                                                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             2. Detailed patch steps                                                                                                                                                             
                                a) Delete lines 99107 (the old single-pass `LIST_FOREACH` + `condition_free` + `assert`).                                                                                       
                                b) Insert the following code at the same location:                                                                                                                               
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                   Condition* condition_free_list_type(Condition *head, ConditionType type) {                                                                                                    
                                       /* If type < 0, remove all nodes safely and return NULL */                                                                                                                
                                       if (type < 0)                                                                                                                                                             
                                               return LIST_CLEAR(conditions, head, condition_free);                                                                                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                       /* Otherwise traverse safely, cache next in macro, unlink and free matching nodes */                                                                                      
                                       LIST_FOREACH_WITH_NEXT(conditions, c, n, head) {                                                                                                                          
                                               if (c->type == type) {                                                                                                                                            
                                                       LIST_REMOVE(conditions, head, c);                                                                                                                         
                                                       condition_free(c);                                                                                                                                        
                                               }                                                                                                                                                                 
                                       }                                                                                                                                                                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                                       return head;                                                                                                                                                              
                                   }                                                                                                                                                                             
                                   ```                                                                                                                                                                           
                                c) Remove the trailing `assert(type >= 0 || !head);`  its redundant when using `LIST_CLEAR`, which guarantees `head == NULL` when all nodes are freed.                         
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             3. Why this works                                                                                                                                                                   
                                - `LIST_CLEAR(conditions, head, condition_free)` is a tested macro in `src/basic/list.h` that safely iterates while caching the next pointer before each                       
                             `free`, then resets the head to `NULL`.                                                                                                                                             
                                - `LIST_FOREACH_WITH_NEXT` declares its own `i` and `n` variables internally, avoiding any external shadowing or unused-variable warnings. It updates `n =                       
                             i->name##_next` before each iteration, so unlinking and freeing `i` (our `c`) doesnt break the loops internal pointer logic.                                                      
                                - `LIST_REMOVE` correctly updates the lists head and neighboring pointers.                                                                                                      
                                - No manual declarations of `c` or `n` appear outside the macros, eliminating the `-Wshadow` errors and unused-variable warnings.                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             4. Preservation of existing behavior                                                                                                                                                
                                - The function signature and return semantics remain unchanged.                                                                                                                  
                                - For `type < 0`, callers receive `NULL` as before (and the old `assert` is implied by `LIST_CLEAR`).                                                                            
                                - For selective removal, nodes with non-matching types stay in place in their original order, and the updated `head` pointer is correctly returned.                              
                                - All existing tests, fuzzing harnesses, and consumers of `condition_free_list_type` continue to work unmodified.                                                                
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             5. Side-effects and mitigations                                                                                                                                                     
                                - By removing the explicit `assert`, we rely on `LIST_CLEAR` to set `head = NULL`. This is consistent with the original contract (`type < 0` implies an empty                    
                             list).                                                                                                                                                                              
                                - No broad exception catches are introduced, and no external libraries or harness code are modified.                                                                             
                                - Potential future type checks remain valid, and the macro-based approach matches patterns used elsewhere in `src/basic/list.h`, minimizing maintenance burden.                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             6. References to code ranges                                                                                                                                                        
                                - Replacement of `condition_free_list_type` functionality:                                                                                                                       
                                  <code_range>src/shared/condition.c:99-107</code_range>                                                                                                                         
                                - Definition of `LIST_CLEAR`, `LIST_FOREACH_WITH_NEXT`, and `LIST_REMOVE`:                                                                                                       
                                  <code_range>src/basic/list.h:47-62</code_range>                                                                                                                                
                                  <code_range>src/basic/list.h:136-142</code_range>                                                                                                                              
                                  <code_range>src/basic/list.h:195-204</code_range>                                                                                                                              
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             This patch fixes the heapuseafterfree by ensuring the next pointer is always captured before any `free`, and it compiles cleanly under `-Werror,-Wshadow`                      
                             without altering any harness or test code.                                                                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
                             </fix_strategy>
